About the Parade

The October Thriver Parade is ADY Life Center's annual fall celebration, coinciding with Breast Cancer Awareness Month. We go beyond awareness to create something more: a vibrant, visible, joyful public space where survivors are honored and community connection happens in real time.

This isn't just a parade â€” it's a public affirmation that thriving is possible. Walk, roll, or cheer as part of a community that celebrates resilience, connection, and the transformative power of joy.

Parade procession with breast cancer survivors, all cancer thrivers, and allies
Thrivership milestone celebrations and survivor recognition
Wellness education stations and local cancer support organization partners
Live entertainment, movement activities, and community connection
Free educational materials on thriving through and beyond cancer

Free & Open Access

Educational Resources

We develop and distribute free educational materials that translate complex research on joy, resilience, and thriving into accessible, actionable information â€” empowering individuals to improve their quality of life after diagnosis and treatment.

Medical care rarely includes comprehensive education about life after treatment. Patients are often told they're "cancer-free" but given little guidance on how to thrive in their new reality. We fill that gap.

Our Story

About ADY Life Center

A Maryland nonprofit incorporated December 2025, built by cancer survivors and community organizers who believe thriving â€” not just surviving â€” is a fundamental human need.

ADY
Ain't Dead Yet
"Major life transitions, illness, addiction recovery, loss, and aging create change â€” but that change can be a doorway to growth rather than merely something to endure."

Joy is Medicine

Research demonstrates that social connection, community support, and joyful practices significantly improve physical and mental health outcomes â€” reducing inflammation, improving immune function, and decreasing depression and anxiety.

Survivors Deserve More

Medical care focuses on disease management. We focus on thriving â€” helping individuals rebuild vibrant, connected, purposeful lives after the medical system has done its work.

Radical Inclusion

All programs are open to everyone regardless of age, diagnosis, race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, disability, or income. We do not restrict services to members or require fees.

Community is the Cure

Social isolation among cancer survivors and chronically ill individuals creates substantial health costs. By building real community, we reduce the burden on healthcare systems and improve lives.

Our Organization

Nonprofit, Transparent & Accountable

ADY Life Center, Inc. was incorporated in Maryland on December 20, 2025, and has applied for recognition of tax-exempt status under Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code (EIN: 41-3716948). Our mission is organized exclusively for charitable and educational purposes.

We are governed by a Board of Directors consisting of founding members with expertise in nonprofit management, community organizing, healthcare, and lived experience with cancer survivorship. Board members serve without compensation.

All fundraising activities support our charitable thriver programs, education, and community events. We are committed to transparency in our operations, finances, and impact.
